# 1. オープニング

Little Saki: Phew! I've never done band stuff before, but playing together like that was really fun!
Little Shiho: Yeah. I guess it was quite rewarding.
Little Honami: I agree. It was exhausting, but also a lot of fun, wasn't it?
Little Ichika: Hey, everyone... I just wanted to say thank you.
Little Ichika: Thanks for going along with my sudden suggestion to form a band and play some Miku songs...
Little Ichika: Also... If you don't mind, can we do this again?
Little Saki: Of course we should do this again! We'll practice again tomorrow, the day after tomorrow, and beyond!
Little Ichika: Yeah! Oh... Was that a shooting star just now?
Little Saki: What? Where? Hey, let's go over to the jungle gym! Maybe we can see some more!
Little Ichika: There's another one!
Little Honami: It's so pretty! Oh yeah, I think I saw something about it on TV this morning.
Little Shiho: Really? Does that mean we can see more if we wait here for a bit?
Little Ichika: A meteor shower... That must look amazing.
Little Saki: ..... *Sigh*
Little Ichika: What's the matter, Saki?
Little Saki: Hehehe... Just making a wish that we could stay like this forever!
Little Saki: Playing together, talking about stuff, watching shooting stars on our way home...
Little Saki: I wish we could keep doing all that together forever!
Little Ichika: I wish we could, too.
Little Honami: Me three!
Little Shiho: Same.
Little Honami: You know what... I have some binoculars and a star chart at home. Let me go get them so we can stargaze together!
Little Shiho: That's a thing? Interesting.
Little Saki: Okay, so let's all go and drop off our instruments at home, then we'll meet back here again after that!
Little Ichika: Yeah!
Teacher: So the object of this sentence...
Ichika: .....
